FuncDecl.Name: GuiMenuButton
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Create a control with a specified default theme.</summary> <param name="themeName">The theme name for retriving a default control template.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: GetLargeImage
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Get the large image for the menu button.</summary> <returns>The large image for the menu button.</returns> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: SetLargeImage
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Set the large image for the menu button.</summary> <param name="value">The large image for the menu button.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: GetImage
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Get the image for the menu button.</summary> <returns>The image for the menu button.</returns> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: SetImage
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Set the image for the menu button.</summary> <param name="value">The image for the menu button.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: GetShortcutText
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Get the shortcut key text for the menu button.</summary> <returns>The shortcut key text for the menu button.</returns> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: SetShortcutText
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Set the shortcut key text for the menu button.</summary> <param name="value">The shortcut key text for the menu button.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: IsSubMenuExists
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Test does the sub menu exist.</summary> <returns>Returns true if the sub menu exists.</returns> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: GetSubMenu
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Get the sub menu. If the sub menu is not created, it returns null.</summary> <returns>The sub menu.</returns> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: CreateSubMenu
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Create the sub menu if necessary. The created sub menu is owned by this menu button.</summary> <returns>The created sub menu.</returns> <param name="subMenuTemplate">The style controller for the sub menu. Set to null to use the default control template.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: SetSubMenu
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Associate a sub menu if there is no sub menu binded in this menu button. The associated sub menu is not owned by this menu button if the "owned" argument is set to false.</summary> <param name="value">The sub menu to associate.</param> <param name="owned">Set to true if the menu is expected to be owned.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: GetOwnedSubMenu
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Test is the sub menu owned by this menu button. If the sub menu is owned, both deleting this menu button or calling <links><link cref="::vl::presentation::controls::GuiMenuButton::DestroySubMenu()@s:vl.presentation.controls.GuiMenuButton" /></links> will delete the sub menu.</summary> <returns>Returns true if the sub menu is owned by this menu button.</returns> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: GetSubMenuOpening
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Test is the sub menu opened.</summary> <returns>Returns true if the sub menu is opened.</returns> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: SetSubMenuOpening
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Open or close the sub menu.</summary> <param name="value">Set to true to open the sub menu.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: GetPreferredMenuClientSize
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Get the preferred client size for the sub menu.</summary> <returns>The preferred client size for the sub menu.</returns> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: SetPreferredMenuClientSize
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Set the preferred client size for the sub menu.</summary> <param name="value">The preferred client size for the sub menu.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: GetCascadeAction
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Test is cascade action enabled. If the cascade action is enabled, when the mouse enter this menu button, the sub menu will be automatically opened if the parent menu is in an active state (see <links><link cref="::vl::presentation::controls::IGuiMenuService::IsActiveState()@s:vl.presentation.controls.IGuiMenuService" /></links>), closing the sub menu will also close the parent menu.</summary> <returns>Returns true if cascade action is enabled.</returns> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: SetCascadeAction
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Enable or disable cascade action.</summary> <param name="value">Set to true to enable cascade action.</param> </Document>
